## Testing Requirements

| Test Type | Category | Command | Required? |
|-----------|----------|---------|-----------|
| Unit | `unit` | `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}} test unit` | Always |
| Integration | `integration` | `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}} test integration` | Always |
| E2E API | `e2e-api` | `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}} test e2e` | When API changes |
| E2E UI | `e2e-ui` | `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}} test e2e` | When UI changes |
| Stress | `stress` | `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}} test stress` | When perf-sensitive |

> **TODO:** Update test commands and add project-specific test types.

### Live-Stack Test Authenticity

- Tests labeled `integration`, `e2e-api`, `e2e-ui`, or otherwise described as live-stack MUST hit the real running system.
- If a test uses request interception such as `route()`, `intercept()`, `msw`, `nock`, or equivalent, it is MOCKED and MUST be classified as `unit`, `functional`, or `ui-unit` instead.
- Project-specific instructions should define the canonical scan command for interception patterns and require gap-filling if a mocked reclassification removes the last real live-stack test.

### Adversarial Regression Tests For Bug Fixes

- Every bug-fix regression test MUST include at least one adversarial case that would fail if the bug were reintroduced.
- Tautological regressions are forbidden: if all fixtures already satisfy the broken filter/gate/path, the regression cannot detect the bug.
- Required tests MUST NOT use bailout returns such as `if (page.url().includes('/login')) { return; }` or equivalent failure-condition early exits.

